1926 - EKCO founded by Eric Kirkham Cole (1901-1966); 
1960 - Ekco merged with Pye to form British Electronic Industries Ltd.;  from 1926 manufactured radios; quickly branched out into Bakelite production (for cases); 
1935 - invested in Scophony Ltd, mechanical television system; wartime production of radar and military wireless sets; post war television and car radio production;
1973 - absorbed into conglomerate; plastics arm continued as Lin Pac Mouldings Limited.

